Description: Well, if youre reading this, it is your turn to go down the Stage Guitars Arlington Texas rabbit hole...over the years ive found out some were made in Korea,Some by Univox and some in Texas...I know 2 brothers owned the company and eventually went out of business...there may or may not have been a Lawsuit on these...the info is hard to come by ,but ive seen it in various forums if you dig deep...anyway...awesome guitar...feels like a lighter Les Paul...but still plenty Beefy at 15 pounds...has that bottom end chunk...loves distortion...needs a cleaning but is playable as is...its been sitting in my mancave for at least 20 years...before that who knows...so do your research and lmk if ya find out anything solid...the case is fairly new & is worth 80plus alone...all the switches and knobs work as they should with no crackle...check out my other items...thanks for looking...i package like a tank and ship fast... the price on this item will not go down...it is a quality guitar on par with a used epi lp that was 499 & sell for 250 350 used...you cant even find this guitar...that alone makes it a worthy investment,and everything works fine...from my time capsule...it rocks hard...dont buy a gibson epihone special or even a standard when you could have this 35+ year old gem at this price....maybe its from Texas...maybe its 80s Univox...its a win win...no Lars Fans...peace did i mention it rocks hard...? Tenaciously...?
